The information carried by each mouse-specific set of time series has been condensed into a correlation matrix, whose generic entry $C_{ij}$ is the Pearson coefficient between time series $X^i$ and $X^j$, defined as

\begin{eqnarray}
C_{ij}&=&\frac{\mbox{Cov}[X^i, X^j]}{\sqrt{\mbox{Var}[X^i]\cdot\mbox{Var}[X^j]}}=\nonumber\\
&=&\frac{\sum_{t=1}^T(X_t^i-m^i)(X^j_t-m^j)}{\sqrt{\sum_{t=1}^T(X^i_t-m^i)^2\cdot\sum_{t=1}^T(X^j_t-m^j)^2}}
\end{eqnarray}

\noindent where $m^i=\frac{\sum_{t=1}^TX^i_t}{T}$ and $T$ is the total temporal length of the series.
